properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore Island VA out 20 nm; Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague VA out 20 nm
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 14 at 4:49PM EST until January 15 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce
visibilities below 1 NM at times through tonight. For the Gale
Watch, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and
waves 3 to 6 ft possible.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague
VA out 20 nm and Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore
Island VA out 20 nm.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 7 AM EST Wednesday.
For the Gale Watch, from Thursday morning through late
Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 AM EST WEDNESDAY... ...GALE WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE THURSDAY NIGHT
